2. Directory Removal with Open Handles
Windows can't delete directories with open files. The get_unique_folder_name function creates then deletes directories:

 1 match std::fs::create_dir(&new_path) {
 2     Ok(()) => {
 3         // On Windows, need to ensure all handles are dropped
 4         drop(std::fs::read_dir(&new_path)?); // Close any directory handles
 5         let _ = std::fs::remove_dir(&new_path);
 6         return new_path;
 7     }
 8     // ...
 9 }

3. Parallel Worker File Locking
Windows file locking is stricter. Multiple workers trying to access the same files could fail:

 1 // Workers might be trying to create/delete files that are still locked
 2 // Need to ensure proper handle cleanup between operations
